description._content:
Program of events to celebrate the 100th anniversary of Deseronto's incorporation as a village.

"Thursday, June 17th, 1971
7:00 p.m. - Parade
8:00 p.m. - Band Concert in Centennial Park - admission 25¢

Friday, June 18th, 1971
9:00 a.m. - 1:00 p.m. - Factory Tours
2:00p.m. - 5:00p.m. - Centennial Tea at Mrs Ross Sexmith's -admissiono 50¢
8:00p.m. - Centennial Jubilee of Music and a play entitled "The Gift of the Drum: Deseronto Public School - admission 50¢ adults, 25¢ children.

Saturday, June 19th,  1971
10:00-12:00a.m. - Antique Display and film "A Place to Stand" - Deseronto Public Library - coffee and donuts - 25¢
1:00p.m. - Ski Show - Centennial Park
2:00p.m. - Plaque unveiling
3:00p.m. - Sweet River Street Band Concert - Centennial Park
4.30p.m. - Ski Show - Centennial Park
8:00p.m. - Centennial Fashion Show - Deseronto Public School - admission 50¢

Sunday, June 20th, 1971
-Centennial Services in Churches
-12:00p.m. Family Picnic - Centennial Pk."

From a collection of materials relating to the 1971 centennial of Deseronto's incorporation as a village.
